- commands start with a black-slash
  * \pi inserts pi symbol
- general command format
  * \command[optinal arg]{required argument}
  * \hypersetup{colorlinks=true, linkcolor=blue}
- commands such as \pi dont take any arguments
- command like \begin{} require an argument
- \documentclass[11pt, twocolumn]{article}
- \frac{numerator}{denominator}
- % this is a comment

- To render text in math mode
  * inline: $x+3$
  * block:  $$x+3$$ or \[x+3\]
    > either $$...$$ or \[...\]
  * whole sections:
    \begin{equation]...\end{equation}
- \documentclass{article}
  \usepackage{asmath}
- \begin{document}
  \end{document}

